paragraph.value: The experimental results on WOZ 2.0 corpus are presented in Table 1.  the three baseline models, BERT+RNN, BERT+RNN+Ontology, and the slot-dependent  SUMBT, showed no significant performance differences. On the other hand, the slot-independent SUMBT which learned the shared information from all across domains and slots significantly outperformed those baselines, resulting in 91.0% joint accuracy.  The proposed model achieved state-of-theart performance in both WOZ 2.0 and MultiWOZ datasets.
